introduction.p:
If S is a matrix in scalar-triangular form with eigenvalue \lambda = \lambda_0 repeated down the diagonal, then \lambda I - S will have form like
N_2 \amp = \begin{bmatrix} 0 \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix} \text{,} \amp N_3 \amp = \begin{bmatrix} 0 \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix} \text{,} \amp N_4 \amp = \begin{bmatrix} 0 \amp \ast \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp \ast \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp \ast \\ 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \amp 0 \end{bmatrix} \text{,}
or similarly for larger sizes.
